The kinetic study was realized for the adsorption equilibrium according to the following protocol: 50 mg of DZCO2 samples immersed in 100 mL of HCrO4− solutions with different concentrations Co for predetermined time intervals. The solutions were separated from adsorbent by centrifugation (4000 rpm, 5 min), and the HCrO4− concentration was analyzed with a UV–visible spectrophotometer (Jasco V-630); HCrO4− absorbs at 348 nm (ε = 1770 cm−1 mol−1 L) (Charlot 1961). The absorbance calibration curves were plotted versus the concentration of HCrO4−. The sampling was performed every 15 min during the first hour and more spaced beyond 1 h. The adsorbed amount Qt (µmol/g), at time t, was calculated from the relation:1Qt=Vm(C0-Ct)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
